Given an integer N, write a program to print the reverse of the number.
If N is negative, the reversed number should also be negative.
Input Format

A single integer N
Constraints

-10^9 <= N <= 10^9
Output Format

Print the reversed integer preserving the sign.
Sample Input 0

1234
Sample Output 0

4321
Sample Input 1

-907
Sample Output 1

-709

import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;

public class Solution {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        int n=sc.nextInt();
        int r=0;
        while(n!=0){
            int last=n%10;
            r=(r*10)+last;
            n=n/10;
        }
        System.out.println(r);
      
    }
}
